subSubSection.paragraph:
Male.
Median lobe (
Fig. 20a, b
) very large and robust, in ventral view very elongated, strongly tapered at tip (
Fig. 20a
). Parameres more elongated than in the other species of the genus. Protarsus somewhat expanded. Mesotarsus less so. Inner edge of mesotibia straight.
